meanings.definition: ヘンリー・スティール・オルコット (人名)
meanings.english_definition: Henry Steel Olcott (1832-1907), an American agriculturalist, journalist, lawyer and co-founder and first president of the Theosophical Society.

etymology.value: Derived from Old English personal name 'Ola' + 'cott' meaning 'Ola's cottage'.
